                            <comment id="89608" author="grussell" created="Wed, 24 Apr 2013 11:11:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;See &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.spring.io/browse/AMQP-260&quot; title=&quot;Hanging thread when using RabbitTransactionManager with a listener container where channelTransacted=true&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AMQP-260&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AMQP-260&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;; prior to that change, when using a RabbitTransactionManager, downstream operations (using the same connection factory) did not use the listener&apos;s channel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A channel registry was added to ensure the resource holder had access to the channel.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, this registry did not take into account the downstream operation might be performed by a &lt;tt&gt;RabbitTemplate&lt;/tt&gt; with a different connection factory.&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;1. Add code to ensure we only reuse the listener&apos;s channel if the downstream component is using the same connection factory.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Add a test case to reproduce the problem and verify it is corrected.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
